etomica.atom.iterator

Interface MoleculesetIteratorTargetable

  • All Superinterfaces:
    AtomsetIterator, MoleculesetIterator
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    MoleculesetIteratorBasisDependent, MoleculesetIteratorPDT
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    MoleculeIteratorAll, MoleculeIteratorMolecule, Mpi1ACell, MpiInterspecies1A, MpiIntraspecies1A, MpiMolecule, PotentialMaster.MoleculeIterator0

    public interface MoleculesetIteratorTargetable
extends MoleculesetIterator
    Interface for an iterator that can be targeted at one or more atoms. Setting a target causes the iterator to produce only those of its iterates that contain the target atom(s). A typical use would be to set an atom as a target for a pair iterator, so the iterator would form only those pairs that contain the targeted atom. The argument can be null, indicating no target.
